other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated measuring up to 1.1 cm and demonstrates a thickened wall with adjacent fat stranding, consistent with appendicitis. There is mild periportal edema. Enlarged uterus containing a large, submucosal fibroid measuring 5.8 x 4.8 cm and a hypodense cystic structure in the right adnexa measuring 1.6 x 1.8 cm, which likely represents a corpus luteum cyst.
